 \"symbol\": \"IonCompileTask\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"js/src/jit/BaselineJIT.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"BaselineScript\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"js/src/jit/JitRuntime.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"JitRuntime\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"js/src/jit/JitOptions.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"JitOptions\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The SpiderMonkey JIT compilation pipeline consists of the following key components located in mozilla-firefox/firefox at js/src/jit/:\\n\\n1. **IonCompile Function** (js/src/jit/Ion.cpp, line 1765): The top-level function `IonCompile` orchestrates the Ion optimizing compiler. It's the entry point for the second-tier JIT compilation pipeline that optimizes and compiles JavaScript code to native machine code. This function is declared in js/src/jit/Ion.h.\\n\\n2. **IonCompileTask** (js/src/jit/IonCompileTask.h and IonCompileTask.cpp): Represents an off-thread compilation task that allows Ion compilation to happen asynchronously. The `IonCompileTask` class (line 27 of IonCompileTask.h) extends HelperThreadTask and manages compilation of scripts in background threads.\\n\\n3. **BaselineScript** (js/src/jit/BaselineJIT.h, line 189): The `BaselineScript` class represents the first-tier JIT compiler output. This is the initial, faster-to-compile JIT tier that provides quick execution before code is optimized by Ion. It's defined in BaselineJIT.h and implemented in BaselineJIT.cpp.\\n\\n4. **JitRuntime** (js/src/jit/JitRuntime.h, line 121): The `JitRuntime` class manages per-runtime JIT state, including tracking off-thread compilation tasks, managing JIT code allocation, and maintaining global JIT infrastructure for each JSRuntime instance.\\n\\n5. **JitOptions** (js/src/jit/JitOptions.h and JitOptions.cpp): The `JitOptions` extern variable (declared in JitOptions.h, implemented in JitOptions.cpp) provides configuration for the JIT compiler, controlling various optimization passes and JIT features. The underlying configuration is defined by the `DefaultJitOptions` struct.\"\n}\n",
